data.name: IDS_CreateMyBiblicalTermsQuery
data.value:
In order to add or edit key terms, you have to begin using a local copy of one of the existing key terms list (i.e. a copy generated, for example, from the Paratext "Major Key Terms" or "All Key Terms" lists or one customized by your entity). At this point, you may want to click 'Cancel' here and then click the "Select Key Terms List" button to select one of the other, existing key terms lists to see if the term you want is present in one of them. If you don't find the term in one of those lists and you want to make an editable key terms list that you can add it to, then select the key terms list that you want to start with (i.e. the "Major" or "All" terms list). Once you've chosen a list to start with, then click this button again to merge (or overwrite, if desired) a new version of the 'My Biblical Terms' list that you will be able to edit.
Beware, though, that the local copy of the key terms list will be stored in your project folder and shared with the other team members (so all members have access and can see the key terms you've added). This means that it will be synchronized to the Internet, which may take a long time the first time (for e.g., the 'All Terms' list is 8MB, the 'Major Terms' list is 4MB). Thereafter, it will only synchronize whatever changes you make, so it won't always be time- consuming, but the first time after creating the local copy will. Also, beware that if you overwrite the editable copy of the 'My Biblical Terms' list, you may be overwriting data that another team member has created and added to. So be sure that you discuss this with the rest of the team before overwriting a list

data.name: HTML_DOM_Prefix
data.value:
<script>
    function OnBibRefJump(link) {
        window.external.OnBibRefJump(link.name);
        return false; // cause the href navigation to not happen
    }
    function OnVerseLineJump(link) {
        window.external.OnVerseLineJump(link.name);
        return false; // cause the href navigation to not happen
    }
    function OnKeyDown() {
        if (window.event.keyCode == 116) {
            // let the form handle it
            window.external.LoadDocument();

            // disable the propagation of the F5 event
            window.event.keyCode = 0;
            window.event.returnValue = false;
            return false;
        }
        else if (window.event.ctrlKey && (window.event.keyCode == 70)) {
            if (window.event.stopPropagation) {
                window.event.stopPropagation();
            }
            else {
                window.event.cancelBubble = true;
                window.event.returnValue = false;
                window.event.keyCode = 0;
            }
            window.external.DoFind();
            return false;
        }
    }
    function textboxSetSelection(strId, iStart, iLen) {
        var oTextbox = document.getElementById(strId);
        var oRange = oTextbox.createTextRange();
        oRange.moveStart("character", iStart);
        oRange.moveEnd("character", -oTextbox.value.length + iStart + iLen);
        oRange.select();
    }
    function textboxSetSelectionTextReturnEndPosition(strId, strNewValue) {
        var oTextbox = document.getElementById(strId);
        var rangeSelection = document.selection.createRange();
        var rangeElement = rangeSelection.duplicate();
        rangeElement.moveToElementText(oTextbox);
        var nEndPoint = 0;
        if (rangeElement.inRange(rangeSelection)) {
            rangeSelection.text = strNewValue;
            rangeSelection.select();
            while (rangeElement.compareEndPoints('StartToEnd', rangeSelection) < 0) {
                rangeElement.moveStart('character', 1);
                nEndPoint++;
            }
        }
        return nEndPoint;
    }
</script>

data.name: HTML_DOM_PrefixPresentation
data.value:
<script type="text/javascript">
function OnBibRefJump(btn)
{
  window.external.OnBibRefJump(btn.id);
  return false; // cause the href navigation to not happen
}
function OnLineOptionsButton(btn)
{
  window.external.OnLineOptionsButton(btn.id);
  return false;
}
function OnVerseLineJump(link)
{
  window.external.OnVerseLineJump(link.name);
  return false; // cause the href navigation to not happen
}
function OnKeyDown(textarea)
{
  if (window.event.keyCode == 116)
  {
    // let the form handle it
    window.external.LoadDocument();

    // disable the propagation of the F5 event
    window.event.keyCode = 0;
    window.event.returnValue = false;
    return false;
  }
  else 
  {
    if (textarea.value == '') 
	{
      textarea.style.visibility = 'visible';
    }
    else 
	{
      textarea.style.visibility = 'hidden';
    }
  }
}
function CallTextareaOnSelect(textarea) 
{
	if (!document.selection) {
		alert("document.selection is null");
		return false;
	}
	if (!textarea.contentWindow) {
		alert("textarea.contentWindow is null");
		return false;
	}
	var allText = textarea.contentWindow.document.selection.createRange().parentElement().innerText;
	var selText = textarea.contentWindow.document.selection.createRange().text;
	return TextareaOnSelect(textarea.id, allText.indexof(selText), selText.length);
}
</script>

So if the rest of the team (Project Facilitators, Consultant, etc) have all: a) done a 'Project', 'Send/receive' to send all of their outstanding changes, and b) upgraded to the new version of OSE, then if you want the project file to be converted to the new format, click 'Yes'

data.name: HTML_ScriptPostFix
data.value:
<script>
var textareas = document.getElementsByTagName("input");
for (var i=0; i < textareas.length; i++)
{
  textareas[i].onchange = function(){return window.external.TextareaOnChange(this.id, this.value);};
  textareas[i].onblur = function(){return window.external.TextareaOnBlur(this.id, this.value);};
  textareas[i].onselect = function(){return CallTextareaOnSelect(this);};
  textareas[i].onfocus = function(){return window.external.TextareaOnFocus(this.id);};
  textareas[i].onkeydown = function(){return OnKeyDown(this);};
}
</script>
